00:49:28,303 --> 00:49:31,431
It's best if you come on
back down with me right now.

731
00:49:31,640 --> 00:49:32,572
I prefer it.

732
00:49:39,615 --> 00:49:41,879
Be careful. It could be loaded.

733
00:49:42,084 --> 00:49:44,018
-Hold on to that.
-What are you doing?

734
00:49:44,219 --> 00:49:47,120
-Checking this serial number.
-I love my grandchildren.

735
00:49:47,322 --> 00:49:51,224
-A little bit higher.
-It's inappropriate to march in here...

736
00:49:51,493 --> 00:49:54,394
...and you expect me to just let you....

737
00:49:54,596 --> 00:49:55,585
What?

738
00:49:56,832 --> 00:49:58,891
I love you, Caroline.

739
00:49:59,835 --> 00:50:02,861
-You're full of shit.
-I logged it in the evidence locker.

740
00:50:03,071 --> 00:50:05,471
-Logged what in?
-The gun that killed Medgar Evers.

741
00:50:05,674 --> 00:50:07,301
-You're full of shit.
-Who?

742
00:50:07,509 --> 00:50:09,374
He says he found the gun.

743
00:50:09,845 --> 00:50:12,780
-You're full of shit.
-That's something to tell Mrs. Evers.

744
00:50:12,981 --> 00:50:15,575
I'm not gonna tell Mrs. Evers.

745
00:50:16,852 --> 00:50:19,980
You've been making those Friday calls
so she'd trust you.

746
00:50:20,189 --> 00:50:25,092
-lf she finds out....
-I can't have her find out.

747
00:50:25,294 --> 00:50:26,921
This can't leave the office.

748
00:50:27,496 --> 00:50:31,933
The only way we're gonna get a new
indictment is if we find something...

749
00:50:32,134 --> 00:50:34,898
...they didn't have 27 years ago.

750
00:50:35,103 --> 00:50:38,436
The way I see it, that something
will come from Beckwith.

751
00:50:38,640 --> 00:50:40,540
Right now,
he's on his mountaintop...

752
00:50:40,742 --> 00:50:43,734
...shooting his mouth off
to anyone who'll listen.

753
00:50:43,946 --> 00:50:47,313
No telling what incriminating thing's
liable to come out of that man.

754
00:50:47,649 --> 00:50:50,345
But if he knows we have
something like this...

755
00:50:50,552 --> 00:50:52,782
...he'll know we're serious
and clam up.

756
00:50:52,988 --> 00:50:56,014
I doubt that Beckwith and Myrlie
speak all that often.

757
00:50:56,291 --> 00:50:58,589
Myrlie speaks to Jerry Mitchell.

758
00:50:59,094 --> 00:51:01,619
Jerry Mitchell speaks to the world.

759
00:51:13,208 --> 00:51:15,938
"You best stop wasting
our taxpayers' money.

760
00:51:16,144 --> 00:51:18,078
Enjoy your drive home."

761
00:51:18,714 --> 00:51:22,150
Nice to see Jackson still
has some concerned citizens.

762
00:51:23,719 --> 00:51:27,086
Well, heck, son,
what did you expect?

763
00:51:27,589 --> 00:51:30,888
I expect people to act like
decent, law-abiding citizens.

764
00:51:31,093 --> 00:51:33,084
This is 1990, for crying out loud.

765
00:51:33,295 --> 00:51:37,959
Of course it is. And we got blacks
and whites playing ball together...

766
00:51:38,166 --> 00:51:42,262
...and on the police force,
in the government, on TV.

767
00:51:42,671 --> 00:51:46,903
We are a fully evolved society.
Aren't we, son?

768
00:51:49,911 --> 00:51:51,208
Let me tell you something:

769
00:51:51,647 --> 00:51:55,640
This country may be legally
integrated, but emotionally...

770
00:51:55,851 --> 00:51:58,376
...we will always be segregated.

771
00:51:58,587 --> 00:52:00,748
I don't know that I accept that.

772
00:52:01,256 --> 00:52:02,348
Of course not.

773
00:52:02,591 --> 00:52:04,286
You're Bobby DeLaughter...

774
00:52:04,493 --> 00:52:07,519
...Mississippi's self-appointed
new civil rights leader.

775
00:52:08,063 --> 00:52:09,052
Barney...

776
00:52:09,331 --> 00:52:11,128
...do we have to talk about this?

777
00:52:11,333 --> 00:52:13,528
No, we do not.

778
00:52:14,903 --> 00:52:17,895
Who all wants some of your
grandpa's famous baby backs?

779
00:52:18,106 --> 00:52:19,698
I do! I do!

780
00:52:30,552 --> 00:52:32,042
You're my son.

781
00:52:32,521 --> 00:52:34,148
I don't want you to get hurt.

782
00:52:37,059 --> 00:52:39,459
In Jackson, Mississippi

783
00:52:40,462 --> 00:52:43,898
In 1963

784
00:52:44,733 --> 00:52:47,930
There lived a man

785
00:52:48,136 --> 00:52:49,262
Who was brave

786
00:52:51,473 --> 00:52:55,466
He fought for freedom

787
00:52:56,478 --> 00:52:57,809
Hello, Mrs. Evers?

788
00:52:58,113 --> 00:52:59,341
It's Bobby DeLaughter.

789
00:53:00,115 --> 00:53:02,447
Nothing earth shattering, no.

790
00:53:02,784 --> 00:53:04,945
We've located all the witnesses...

791
00:53:05,153 --> 00:53:08,179
...but without the original
trial transcript...

792
00:53:08,390 --> 00:53:10,381
...it's tough piecing the case together.

793
00:53:11,893 --> 00:53:13,724
No, ma'am, that's about it.

794
00:53:14,629 --> 00:53:18,190
-I wish I had more to report.
-Hang up the phone.

795
00:53:18,433 --> 00:53:21,402
-Hang up the phone.
-I hope I'll have something...

796
00:53:21,603 --> 00:53:23,935
...a little more exciting next Friday.

797
00:53:24,773 --> 00:53:26,070
-You too.
-Hang up.

798
00:53:26,675 --> 00:53:29,109
I'll call you next Friday, Mrs. Evers.

799
00:53:30,045 --> 00:53:31,979
Thank you. Goodbye.

800
00:53:32,447 --> 00:53:33,607
What is going on?

801
00:53:33,849 --> 00:53:37,285
Would a confession by Mr. Beckwith
qualify as exciting?

802
00:53:38,120 --> 00:53:38,950
What do you got?

803
00:53:39,721 --> 00:53:40,745
You know Jack Ables?

804
00:53:40,956 --> 00:53:41,786
The lawyer?

805
00:53:41,990 --> 00:53:45,448
He's representing a movie studio
in a defamation of character suit...

806
00:53:45,660 --> 00:53:50,154
...brought by a couple Klansmen.
While he was doing his research...

807
00:53:50,365 --> 00:53:52,026
...he came across that.

808
00:53:53,535 --> 00:53:55,002
"Klandestine."

809
00:53:55,470 --> 00:53:57,097
It was written 20 years ago...

810
00:53:57,305 --> 00:54:01,002
...about this Klan titan turned
FBl informant, Delmar Dennis.

811
00:54:01,209 --> 00:54:06,146
On page 38, he talks about attending
a Klan rally in August of 1965.

812
00:54:06,481 --> 00:54:08,642
Guess who was a motivational speaker?

813
00:54:10,952 --> 00:54:12,442
-Beckwith?
-Our boy.

814
00:54:12,654 --> 00:54:13,882
Listen to this.

815
00:54:14,289 --> 00:54:15,756
And I quote:

816
00:54:16,158 --> 00:54:19,992
" Killing that nigger gave me no more
discomfort than our wives endure...

817
00:54:20,195 --> 00:54:22,186
...when they give birth
to our children."

818
00:54:22,597 --> 00:54:24,360
Sounds like a confession to me.

819
00:54:24,566 --> 00:54:28,832
Let's run down this Delmar Dennis.
We need to have a chat with him.

820
00:54:37,012 --> 00:54:39,606
$100 says old Delmar
chickens out on us.

821
00:54:39,915 --> 00:54:43,351
He's probably hiding in the woods,
shitting in his drawers.

822
00:54:51,827 --> 00:54:53,727
Where the hell is this place?

823
00:54:53,962 --> 00:54:55,827
This guy informed on the Klan.

824
00:54:56,064 --> 00:55:00,626
He could have made a deal with them
to save his butt by delivering us.

825
00:55:00,836 --> 00:55:02,599
That's a happy thought.

826
00:56:08,970 --> 00:56:10,938
One of you Bobby DeLaughter?

827
00:56:12,841 --> 00:56:16,072
Holding rallies and burning
crosses is one thing...

828
00:56:16,278 --> 00:56:19,577
...but when they killed them
three kids up in Neshoba County...

829
00:56:19,781 --> 00:56:22,079
-...freedom riders--
-Goodman, Chaney, Schwerner?

830
00:56:23,785 --> 00:56:26,515
That made a lot of people
come to their senses.

831
00:56:26,922 --> 00:56:30,551
That's why I decided
to go undercover for the FBl.

832
00:56:31,293 --> 00:56:34,592
I need to ask you if what
you say in that book happened.

833
00:56:34,796 --> 00:56:38,892
That part about Beckwith's speech
at that Klan rally. Is that a fact?

834
00:56:39,768 --> 00:56:40,962
It's a fact.

835
00:56:41,336 --> 00:56:44,601
I was shocked, and I remember
thinking how stupid he was...

836
00:56:44,806 --> 00:56:47,798
...shooting off his mouth
like that in front of 100 men.

837
00:56:48,043 --> 00:56:50,944
-Did you report that to the FBl?
-Sure, I did.

838
00:56:51,179 --> 00:56:54,376
But Beckwith was a white man
accused of killing a black.

839
00:56:54,583 --> 00:56:58,246
The FBl wasn't gonna blow my cover
on a case they couldn't win.

840
00:56:58,453 --> 00:57:00,444
They were saving me
for Neshoba because--

841
00:57:00,855 --> 00:57:02,413
Two of the victims were white.

842
00:57:09,664 --> 00:57:12,792
Mr. Dennis,
if I can't build the case...

843
00:57:13,001 --> 00:57:16,732
...I give you my word that
we never had this conversation.

844
00:57:17,739 --> 00:57:19,172
But if I can...

845
00:57:19,374 --> 00:57:20,932
...will you testify?

846
00:57:24,779 --> 00:57:27,043
Byron De La Beckwith
is the craziest...

847
00:57:27,248 --> 00:57:30,376
...most dangerous son of a bitch
I ever come across.

848
00:57:30,685 --> 00:57:33,279
He's so crazy even
the Klan's afraid of him.

849
00:57:33,521 --> 00:57:34,818
He's an old man now.

850
00:57:35,023 --> 00:57:39,460
That old man is probably more dangerous
today than he was 30 years ago.

851
00:57:40,428 --> 00:57:42,988
Mr. Dennis, we need your help.

852
00:57:43,932 --> 00:57:46,162
I can't make no promises.

853
00:57:50,305 --> 00:57:52,205
You know something, Mr. Dennis?

854
00:57:52,641 --> 00:57:54,165
Six months I've worked this case.

855
00:57:54,376 --> 00:57:56,936
A lot of people have told me
to give it up.

856
00:57:57,145 --> 00:58:00,410
" It's 27 years old.
Let sleeping dogs lie."

857
00:58:00,615 --> 00:58:03,049
But I don't see
what difference it makes...

858
00:58:03,251 --> 00:58:05,412
...if a man was
bushwhacked yesterday...

859
00:58:05,620 --> 00:58:08,521
...today or 27 damn years ago.

860
00:58:08,723 --> 00:58:10,384
Murder is murder.

861
00:58:11,126 --> 00:58:14,493
It's still my job to bring
the son of a bitch to justice.

862
00:58:14,696 --> 00:58:16,493
It's still your job to help me.

863
00:58:16,731 --> 00:58:20,098
No. I did my job.
I testified against the Klan.

864
00:58:20,301 --> 00:58:22,701
They shot out my windows,
blew up my car.

865
00:58:22,904 --> 00:58:25,668
They hunted and harassed me
for 25 years!

866
00:58:26,074 --> 00:58:28,201
Don't that get me even
for the wrong I done?

867
00:58:29,477 --> 00:58:32,139
We never get even
for the wrong we've done.

868
00:58:45,894 --> 00:58:47,794
If I do this thing...

869
00:58:50,231 --> 00:58:52,256
...you gotta promise me protection.

870
00:59:02,143 --> 00:59:03,337
What's going on?

871
00:59:04,579 --> 00:59:05,409
Stop that.

872
00:59:05,613 --> 00:59:06,978
Stop that. IKnock it off.

873
00:59:07,215 --> 00:59:08,045
Enough of that!

874
00:59:08,349 --> 00:59:10,817
-What's going on?
-Eddy called you a nigger lover.

875
00:59:11,019 --> 00:59:14,386
My dad says you're after a man
for something that isn't even a crime.

876
00:59:14,622 --> 00:59:17,955
That's enough fighting, son.
You get on home. Go on home.

877
00:59:18,159 --> 00:59:19,592
Let me take a look at you.

878
00:59:19,794 --> 00:59:23,491
My God. Get in this house.
What's gotten into you?

879
00:59:28,069 --> 00:59:30,697
All this fighting.
All this name-calling.

880
00:59:31,206 --> 00:59:32,503
Is this what you want?

881
00:59:32,741 --> 00:59:34,436
To drag your children into this?

882
00:59:34,676 --> 00:59:37,770
What would you have me do?
Let a murderer go free?

883
00:59:38,146 --> 00:59:41,377
I'd never tell you your business.
I'm thinking about the children.

884
00:59:41,583 --> 00:59:44,882
I don't understand why every
decent person in this state...

885
00:59:45,086 --> 00:59:48,283
...isn't sickened by what
happened here 27 years ago.

886
00:59:48,490 --> 00:59:50,754
-Oh, Bobby.
-You're not, are you?

887
00:59:50,959 --> 00:59:53,359
-Not in front of the children.
-Why not?

888
00:59:53,595 --> 00:59:55,028
I was just a kid...

889
00:59:55,230 --> 00:59:58,324
...and I still remember you
and your friends discussing it.

890
00:59:58,533 --> 01:00:02,025
And I recollect someone saying,
"That nigger needed to be shot."

891
01:00:03,304 --> 01:00:05,465
I never said a hateful
thing like that.

892
01:00:05,673 --> 01:00:09,404
-You didn't cry, did you?
-I can't say that I shed any tears--

893
01:00:09,611 --> 01:00:13,172
Had it been our beloved governor,
Ross Barnett, got himself shot...

894
01:00:13,381 --> 01:00:16,111
...you would've been
bawling your eyes out.

895
01:00:16,317 --> 01:00:20,515
Evers left a young widow and three
little kids. Why didn't you cry?

896
01:00:20,722 --> 01:00:22,849
-I don't wanna discuss this now.
-Why?

897
01:00:23,057 --> 01:00:25,548
Because he tried to destroy
our way of life.

898
01:00:25,760 --> 01:00:27,455
And he succeeded all too well.

899
01:00:27,662 --> 01:00:30,426
This state's going to hell
on account of integration.

900
01:00:30,632 --> 01:00:33,430
That's a fact. If you think
they appreciate one thing...

901
01:00:33,635 --> 01:00:35,432
...we gave them, you're crazy.

902
01:00:35,637 --> 01:00:38,128
-Tiger, how do you feel?
-I'm all right.

903
01:00:38,339 --> 01:00:41,831
-Your son has one tough nose.
-So it's not broken?

904
01:00:43,111 --> 01:00:46,205
It'll be tender for a couple days,
then it'll be good as new.

905
01:00:46,481 --> 01:00:48,176
Thank you. I appreciate it.

906
01:00:48,383 --> 01:00:49,782
You're welcome.

907
01:00:50,518 --> 01:00:51,917
Thank you, ma'am.

908
01:00:57,692 --> 01:01:00,092
Are you the one involved
in this Medgar Evers thing?

909
01:01:02,297 --> 01:01:03,730
Yes, I am.

910
01:01:04,265 --> 01:01:07,757
I think what you're trying to do
is very important.

911
01:01:11,873 --> 01:01:13,738
Thank you very much.

912
01:01:29,357 --> 01:01:31,882
I don't want you kids getting
into anymore fights.

913
01:01:32,093 --> 01:01:35,062
-But he called you a--
-I don't care what he called me.

914
01:01:35,263 --> 01:01:38,926
It doesn't bother me. You gotta
learn not to let it bother you.

915
01:01:39,133 --> 01:01:42,296
A lot of people around here
don't like what Daddy's doing now.

916
01:01:42,637 --> 01:01:44,264
What are you doing, Daddy?

917
01:01:45,807 --> 01:01:48,970
I'm trying to put a bad man in jail.

918
01:01:49,544 --> 01:01:51,478
Mama says what you're doing is wrong.

919
01:01:51,679 --> 01:01:54,944
Grandma said Edgar Mevers
is ruining our life.

920
01:01:59,854 --> 01:02:03,620
Medgar Evers was a good guy
who tried to help people.

921
01:02:03,825 --> 01:02:06,385
Did he try to beat the bad guys?

922
01:02:06,594 --> 01:02:10,223
Yes, he did. He fought
so that black people...

923
01:02:10,431 --> 01:02:13,457
...could eat in the same restaurants,
swim in the same pools...

924
01:02:13,668 --> 01:02:17,399
...shop in the same stores and go
to the same schools as white people.

925
01:02:17,605 --> 01:02:18,629
What's wrong with that?

926
01:02:18,840 --> 01:02:19,932
Nothing.

927
01:02:21,075 --> 01:02:23,805
But you'll hear people say
all kinds of bad things...

928
01:02:24,012 --> 01:02:25,673
...about what your daddy's doing.

929
01:02:25,880 --> 01:02:28,815
They're gonna tease you,
try to pick fights.

930
01:02:29,183 --> 01:02:30,946
But no matter what they do...

931
01:02:31,519 --> 01:02:33,680
...I want you to walk away.

932
01:02:34,722 --> 01:02:36,781
What if they say
something really mean?

933
01:02:36,991 --> 01:02:40,586
They're only words. They can't
hurt you unless you let them.

934
01:02:40,795 --> 01:02:43,263
Is this about sticks and stones?

935
01:02:43,464 --> 01:02:46,126
That's exactly what this is about.

936
01:02:46,434 --> 01:02:48,163
Y'all understand what I'm saying?

937
01:02:48,369 --> 01:02:49,461
Yes, sir.

938
01:02:49,804 --> 01:02:50,964
All right.

939
01:02:51,272 --> 01:02:52,671
All y'all get on to bed now.

940
01:02:54,175 --> 01:02:55,369
Good night.

941
01:03:17,498 --> 01:03:21,025
I heard you had a little visit
with my friend Delmar.

942
01:03:21,235 --> 01:03:22,293
Mr. Beckwith?

943
01:03:22,670 --> 01:03:26,231
Next time you see old Delmar,
you tell him for me...

944
01:03:26,507 --> 01:03:28,532
...there are a lot
of dark, winding roads...

945
01:03:28,743 --> 01:03:33,339
... between the backwoods of Louisiana
and a courtroom in Mississippi.

946
01:03:33,915 --> 01:03:36,509
A man could get lost.

947
01:03:46,294 --> 01:03:47,921
Claire, what's the matter?

948
01:03:48,463 --> 01:03:50,556
The ghost's in my room again.

949
01:03:54,435 --> 01:03:56,426
Let's see what we can do.

950
01:03:59,374 --> 01:04:01,604
-Where is he?
-Sitting right there.

951
01:04:01,809 --> 01:04:03,333
Oh, right.

952
01:04:05,046 --> 01:04:07,105
Daddy, sing "Dixie."

953
01:04:09,117 --> 01:04:10,880
Hop into bed, sweetie.

954
01:04:21,429 --> 01:04:22,521
Sing.

955
01:04:24,065 --> 01:04:27,694
You know, sweetie, maybe
" Dixie" is not the right song.

956
01:04:28,169 --> 01:04:30,535
Maybe that's why
this ghost keeps coming back.

957
01:04:30,738 --> 01:04:32,729
-But you said--
-I know, baby.

958
01:04:33,408 --> 01:04:36,775
But I'm not so sure
that all ghosts like "Dixie."

959
01:04:36,978 --> 01:04:39,742
But how do we know
what this ghost likes?

960
01:04:40,314 --> 01:04:44,774
Seeing as this is your special ghost,
maybe he'll like your favorite song.

961
01:04:44,986 --> 01:04:46,578
"Old MacDonald"?

962
01:04:46,788 --> 01:04:48,415
Let's give it a try.

963
01:04:50,425 --> 01:04:52,416
Old MacDonald had a farm

964
01:04:52,693 --> 01:04:54,251
E-I-E-I-O

965
01:04:54,462 --> 01:04:56,396
And on that farm he had a--

966
01:04:56,597 --> 01:04:57,495
What?

967
01:04:57,999 --> 01:04:59,159
A ghost?

968
01:05:01,169 --> 01:05:03,399
And on that farm he had a ghost

969
01:05:03,604 --> 01:05:05,094
E-I-E-I-O

970
01:05:05,440 --> 01:05:07,408
With a boo boo here
And a boo boo there

971
01:05:07,608 --> 01:05:10,236
Here a boo, there a boo
Everywhere a boo boo

972
01:05:24,058 --> 01:05:25,582
You wanted to have lunch
to talk about Burt's nose?

973
01:05:26,360 --> 01:05:27,588
No, actually, l....

974
01:05:27,795 --> 01:05:29,285
I didn't think so.

975
01:05:31,866 --> 01:05:33,697
So then, this is a date?

976
01:05:35,136 --> 01:05:36,262
Apparently.

977
01:05:36,704 --> 01:05:38,501
In the hospital cafeteria?

978
01:05:38,706 --> 01:05:43,143
I took a chance. I thought
it would either be stupid or charming.

979
01:05:43,845 --> 01:05:44,812
What do you think?

980
01:05:45,246 --> 01:05:46,838
Is there a third choice?

981
01:05:47,048 --> 01:05:47,980
Extremely charming?

982
01:05:48,182 --> 01:05:49,706
That's the one.

983
01:05:51,986 --> 01:05:53,715
How'd you get into all this?

984
01:05:54,155 --> 01:05:56,146
You want the standard answer
or the truth?

985
01:05:56,357 --> 01:05:57,881
How about a little of both?

986
01:05:59,894 --> 01:06:01,987
I always liked helping people...

987
01:06:02,196 --> 01:06:03,356
...and I like the hours.

988
01:06:03,631 --> 01:06:04,962
Which answer was that?

989
01:06:05,166 --> 01:06:06,531
A little of both.

990
01:06:06,767 --> 01:06:10,328
But I do like that I work
one week on and one week off.

991
01:06:10,705 --> 01:06:11,865
Can't beat that.

992
01:06:12,073 --> 01:06:15,270
Have to be careful not to shop
too much in that week off.

993
01:06:15,476 --> 01:06:18,070
That can kill you.
What about you?

994
01:06:18,746 --> 01:06:21,544
I wanted to be a lawyer
since I was a little kid.

995
01:06:21,749 --> 01:06:23,376
I watched Perry Mason...

996
01:06:23,584 --> 01:06:26,519
...all the time.
I identified with him.

997
01:06:26,754 --> 01:06:29,222
-But he was a defense attorney.
-I know.

998
01:06:29,690 --> 01:06:32,557
Later, I realized the only way
he ever won a case...

999
01:06:32,760 --> 01:06:35,354
...is if some guy jumped up
and yelled, "I did it!"

1000
01:06:35,563 --> 01:06:38,760
That didn't happen often,
so I switched to the other side.

1001
01:06:39,100 --> 01:06:41,432
I think it's a good thing you did.

1002
01:06:44,038 --> 01:06:46,472
You would be in
the minority these days.

1003
01:06:47,742 --> 01:06:50,939
There are a lot more people
on your side than you think.

1004
01:06:52,046 --> 01:06:55,106
You're not saying that because
I bought you a lime Jell-O?

1005
01:06:56,350 --> 01:06:58,784
Well, it is the way
to a woman's heart.

1006
01:07:01,389 --> 01:07:05,826
But if you could pull this off,
it'd do Mississippi a whole lot of good.

1007
01:07:07,562 --> 01:07:08,790
And if I don't?

1008
01:07:10,398 --> 01:07:12,559
I'll pretend I never met you.

1009
01:07:20,074 --> 01:07:23,009
I have renewed faith
in the institution of marriage.

1010
01:07:23,211 --> 01:07:25,577
I can't get enough
of my hunk of burning love.

1011
01:07:25,780 --> 01:07:27,748
Not now, Clara May!

1012
01:07:30,418 --> 01:07:31,908
Clara Mayfield.

1013
01:07:33,321 --> 01:07:35,915
-It's Jerry Mitchell.
-I'll take it.

1014
01:07:41,996 --> 01:07:44,556
-I know you have the gun.
-We've been over this.

1015
01:07:44,765 --> 01:07:47,063
I know you found it
in Russel Moore's den.

1016
01:07:47,935 --> 01:07:52,395
There'll be a story about how the
D.A. Iied to the people of Jackson...

1017
01:07:52,607 --> 01:07:55,303
...and how Bobby DeLaughter
lied to Myrlie Evers.

1018
01:07:55,509 --> 01:07:58,034
I'm calling to see
if you care to comment.

1019
01:07:58,246 --> 01:08:00,077
You've explained why
you lied to the press.

1020
01:08:00,281 --> 01:08:02,806
You still have not explained
why you lied to me.

1021
01:08:03,017 --> 01:08:05,577
I told you. Jerry Mitchell
is a loose cannon.

1022
01:08:05,786 --> 01:08:08,755
This case was so delicate,
I didn't want to take chances.

1023
01:08:08,956 --> 01:08:12,949
I'm the last person on earth who
would jeopardize this investigation.

1024
01:08:13,160 --> 01:08:15,594
There's something
you're not telling me.

1025
01:08:15,796 --> 01:08:18,663
I swear to God, there is no cover-up.

1026
01:08:18,866 --> 01:08:21,926
You fully intend to seek
an indictment and a new trial?

1027
01:08:22,136 --> 01:08:24,331
That's what we've
been working toward.

1028
01:08:24,538 --> 01:08:26,631
I thought so, Mr. DeLaughter.

1029
01:08:27,041 --> 01:08:28,474
I thought so.

1030
01:08:28,776 --> 01:08:32,337
This latest revelation only proves
what we've suspected all along.

1031
01:08:32,546 --> 01:08:36,607
Peters and DeLaughter are just putting
on a show for the black community.

1032
01:08:36,817 --> 01:08:40,844
As far as I'm concerned, they're nothing
but a pair of lying racists...

1033
01:08:41,055 --> 01:08:42,682
...who never, I repeat, never...

1034
01:08:42,890 --> 01:08:45,859
...had any intention
of prosecuting this case.

1035
01:08:47,895 --> 01:08:49,055
You wanted to see me?

1036
01:08:49,263 --> 01:08:51,163
Come on, sit down.

1037
01:08:54,001 --> 01:08:58,062
You don't mind being seen in
the same room with a "lying racist"?

1038
01:08:58,873 --> 01:09:00,670
I don't mind if you don't.

1039
01:09:02,343 --> 01:09:03,708
You know Pat Bennett?

1040
01:09:04,245 --> 01:09:07,180
Sure, she's one of the best
lawyers in the state.

1041
01:09:08,683 --> 01:09:10,207
Why are we talking about her?

1042
01:09:11,519 --> 01:09:14,682
I thought she might be able
to help you on the case.

1043
01:09:15,589 --> 01:09:17,853
I've got it under control, Ed.

1044
01:09:20,261 --> 01:09:22,889
You have your share of
the 93 capital murder cases...

1045
01:09:23,097 --> 01:09:25,429
...we have waiting for trial
under control?

1046
01:09:26,200 --> 01:09:28,498
What new excuse would
you suggest I give...

1047
01:09:28,703 --> 01:09:32,002
...to the families as to why those
who've murdered their loved ones...

1048
01:09:32,206 --> 01:09:33,935
...have yet to see a courtroom?

1049
01:09:34,608 --> 01:09:38,203
I'm just curious.
The fact that Pat Bennett is black...

1050
01:09:38,412 --> 01:09:41,074
...wouldn't have anything to do
with this, would it?

1051
01:09:41,816 --> 01:09:43,977
I'm not gonna dignify that.

1052
01:09:45,986 --> 01:09:49,478
Whatever you may think,
this is not the Bobby DeLaughter case.

1053
01:09:49,690 --> 01:09:53,126
This is a case against the peace
and dignity of Mississippi.

1054
01:09:54,061 --> 01:09:56,495
Monday morning, I'm making a change.

1055
01:10:01,602 --> 01:10:05,003
You're about to hear the testimony
of a fingerprint expert...

1056
01:10:05,206 --> 01:10:09,506
...concerning evidence he claims
to have identified in a certain glass.

1057
01:10:09,710 --> 01:10:11,371
You're entitled to consider...

1058
01:10:11,579 --> 01:10:15,413
... the prosecution's failure to make
the glass available to the defense.

1059
01:10:15,616 --> 01:10:20,144
It is permissible that for one fact
alone to raise a doubt in your minds...

1060
01:10:20,354 --> 01:10:22,754
... that will require
Mrs. Savage's acquittal.

1061
01:10:22,957 --> 01:10:26,290
-Can he do that?
-This is my case, damn it.

1062
01:10:26,494 --> 01:10:28,519
How dare they say
I'm putting on a show?

1063
01:10:28,729 --> 01:10:32,096
Only two people care about
this case, and I'm one of them.

1064
01:10:32,299 --> 01:10:36,065
If anybody's putting on a show,
they are. The only thing they' re--

1065
01:10:36,737 --> 01:10:40,264
They're only trying to stir up
emotions and position themselves...

1066
01:10:40,474 --> 01:10:42,908
...as the saviors
of the black community.

1067
01:10:51,018 --> 01:10:52,178
Where you going?

1068
01:11:11,372 --> 01:11:14,170
This is Bobby DeLaughter.
I hope I didn't disturb you.

1069
01:11:15,843 --> 01:11:17,936
This won't take but a minute, ma'am.

1070
01:11:19,346 --> 01:11:21,576
When I started off,
I had nothing more than...

1071
01:11:21,782 --> 01:11:24,774
...a couple of pages
in an old police report.

1072
01:11:25,553 --> 01:11:28,716
I spent the better part of a year
bumping up against dead witnesses...

1073
01:11:28,923 --> 01:11:30,914
...and tracking down live ones.

1074
01:11:31,125 --> 01:11:34,458
My car's been vandalized,
my son's been in a fight...

1075
01:11:34,662 --> 01:11:38,257
...and I've been called ugly things
by every racist in Mississippi.

1076
01:11:38,466 --> 01:11:40,559
Now, when there's a chance
for an indictment...

1077
01:11:40,768 --> 01:11:42,929
...I've gotta fight off
black politicians too.

1078
01:11:43,137 --> 01:11:47,267
I'm sorry I lied about the gun,
but I've made a commitment to this case.

1079
01:11:47,475 --> 01:11:48,669
I'll be goddamned--

1080
01:11:48,876 --> 01:11:51,709
Pardon me, if I give it up
to some special prosecutor...

1081
01:11:51,912 --> 01:11:54,312
...I don't care if he's
black, green or blue.

1082
01:11:54,515 --> 01:11:57,575
I'm committed and I'm asking you
to make a commitment to me.

1083
01:11:57,785 --> 01:12:00,515
If you do, I'll ride this thing
to the finish line...

1084
01:12:00,721 --> 01:12:02,985
...or collapse
heading in that direction.

1085
01:12:04,558 --> 01:12:07,186
Thank you for your call,
Mr. DeLaughter.

1086
01:12:11,632 --> 01:12:14,032
The hell with her!
She's like all the rest.

1087
01:12:14,235 --> 01:12:18,365
The white world hasn't gone out
of its way to make her trusting.

1088
01:12:18,572 --> 01:12:20,437
When does it start?
What do I have to do?

1089
01:12:20,641 --> 01:12:23,633
We had a real chance to send
a message to this country...

1090
01:12:23,844 --> 01:12:26,813
...that Mississippi isn't
a bunch of redneck racists.

1091
01:12:27,014 --> 01:12:31,110
My mother was right. We should
separate and let the South rise again.

1092
01:12:31,318 --> 01:12:33,445
-You don't believe that.
-Why not?

1093
01:12:33,654 --> 01:12:35,144
She doesn't want my help.

1094
01:12:35,356 --> 01:12:37,790
I'm just another white man
putting her in her place.

1095
01:12:37,992 --> 01:12:40,483
She sees no difference
between me and Beckwith.

1096
01:12:40,694 --> 01:12:42,594
-You didn't tell her about the gun.
-Right.

1097
01:12:42,863 --> 01:12:46,890
If I had it to do over again,
I still wouldn't have told her.

1098
01:12:47,101 --> 01:12:51,060
IKeeping the discovery of the murder
weapon a secret was a good strategy.

1099
01:12:51,272 --> 01:12:55,402
It wouldn't bother her a lick if I was
black. I'd just be a smart lawyer.

1100
01:12:56,043 --> 01:12:58,238
You can't have it both ways.

1101
01:12:58,579 --> 01:13:00,308
What do you mean by that?

1102
01:13:01,882 --> 01:13:04,578
You said the reason you didn't
tell her about the gun...

1103
01:13:04,785 --> 01:13:07,413
...was that you were afraid
she would leak the story.

1104
01:13:07,621 --> 01:13:10,715
You can't expect her to trust you,
if you don't trust her.

1105
01:13:28,909 --> 01:13:32,140
I want you to meet with Pat Bennett
and bring her up to speed.

1106
01:13:33,948 --> 01:13:34,972
Fine.

1107
01:13:36,317 --> 01:13:37,750
It's for the best.

1108
01:13:38,886 --> 01:13:40,478
If you say so.

1109
01:14:03,477 --> 01:14:05,468
I'm going out.
You want something?

1110
01:14:05,679 --> 01:14:09,410
I'd like a Mercedes convertible,
but I'd settle for a Dr. Pepper.

1111
01:15:04,938 --> 01:15:08,339
There are four important
things in my life:

1112
01:15:09,243 --> 01:15:11,370
Medgar, Walter...

1113
01:15:11,679 --> 01:15:13,044
...my children...

1114
01:15:13,347 --> 01:15:14,746
...and this...

1115
01:15:15,382 --> 01:15:18,681
...the original
court-certified transcript.

1116
01:15:19,253 --> 01:15:21,813
I've kept this for 27 years...

1117
01:15:22,122 --> 01:15:24,386
...through three district attorneys.

1118
01:15:24,591 --> 01:15:26,491
Once I give this up...

1119
01:15:26,694 --> 01:15:29,561
...I know that it may be gone forever.

1120
01:15:39,206 --> 01:15:41,766
I don't believe you'll find
anymore opposition...

1121
01:15:41,975 --> 01:15:44,466
...to your continuing
to handle this case.

1122
01:15:45,779 --> 01:15:47,041
Thank you, ma'am.

1123
01:15:49,950 --> 01:15:52,043
It's truly appreciated.

1124
01:15:53,020 --> 01:15:55,284
Let's get the son of a bitch.

1125
01:15:56,557 --> 01:15:57,956
My pleasure.

1126
01:16:00,094 --> 01:16:02,187
The decision by the D.A.'s office...

1127
01:16:02,396 --> 01:16:06,355
...to re-open the 27-year-old murder
case of Byron De La Beckwith...

1128
01:16:06,567 --> 01:16:08,228
...continues to cause controversy.

1129
01:16:08,569 --> 01:16:11,504
Citizens of Jackson are concerned...

1130
01:16:11,705 --> 01:16:15,004
... that taxpayers' money is being
used to dig up the past.

1131
01:16:15,209 --> 01:16:18,940
The grand jury handed down an
indictment of Byron De La Beckwith...

1132
01:16:19,146 --> 01:16:22,138
...in the murder of
civil rights leader Medgar Evers.

1133
01:16:22,349 --> 01:16:23,873
Extradition in the Beckwith case...

1134
01:16:24,084 --> 01:16:27,315
...is seen as a stumbling
block for the D.A.'s office.

1135
01:16:27,521 --> 01:16:29,887
I plan to fight repossession--
What's the word?

1136
01:16:30,090 --> 01:16:33,253
Extradition tooth, nail and claw!

1137
01:16:33,794 --> 01:16:36,786
In an attempt to replace
a lost autopsy report...

1138
01:16:36,997 --> 01:16:40,763
... the D.A.'s office of Hinds County
today received permission...

1139
01:16:40,968 --> 01:16:43,061
...by the Evers family
to exhume the body...

1140
01:16:43,270 --> 01:16:46,706
...of slain civil rights leader
Medgar Evers.

1141
01:16:47,374 --> 01:16:50,901
The body, buried in
Arlington National Cemetery in 1963...

1142
01:16:51,111 --> 01:16:53,773
... was found in remarkably
near-perfect condition.

1143
01:16:57,885 --> 01:17:00,911
After 18 months, extradition was
finally granted...

1144
01:17:01,121 --> 01:17:03,089
...in the case
of Byron De La Beckwith...

1145
01:17:03,290 --> 01:17:07,158
... the man accused of slaying
civil rights leader Medgar Evers.

1146
01:17:08,228 --> 01:17:12,756
Beckwith will face murder charges
30 years after the initial two trials...

1147
01:17:12,966 --> 01:17:16,094
...for the same offense
ended in hung juries.

1148
01:17:16,303 --> 01:17:17,167
Thank you, son.

1149
01:17:17,471 --> 01:17:19,166
" I first received the call...

1150
01:17:19,373 --> 01:17:21,307
...at 9 :42 p. m...

1151
01:17:21,508 --> 01:17:25,205
...on the night of June 12, 1963.

1152
01:17:26,980 --> 01:17:29,608
My partner and I responded
and proceeded to the crime scene...

1153
01:17:29,817 --> 01:17:33,150
...Iocated at 2332 Guynes Street."

1154
01:17:33,487 --> 01:17:35,148
That's pretty good, Benny...

1155
01:17:35,355 --> 01:17:38,290
...but just because you read
the part of a dead witness...

1156
01:17:38,492 --> 01:17:41,393
...doesn't mean you have to
act like you're actually dead.

1157
01:17:41,595 --> 01:17:42,994
I'm doing my best.

1158
01:17:43,197 --> 01:17:44,664
I know you are.

1159
01:17:44,865 --> 01:17:47,356
Medgar Evers' autopsy report
just came in.

1160
01:17:48,001 --> 01:17:51,334
You're not gonna believe this.
He's still dead.

1161
01:17:51,805 --> 01:17:52,999
Thank you, Clara.

1162
01:17:53,207 --> 01:17:56,665
I got off the phone with Charles Evers.
He won't come to the trial.

1163
01:17:56,877 --> 01:17:57,707
Did he say why?

1164
01:17:57,911 --> 01:17:59,173
He wouldn't say.

1165
01:17:59,379 --> 01:18:01,677
Get me the address
of his radio station.

1166
01:18:01,882 --> 01:18:04,043
They found a bullet fragment
in the body.

1167
01:18:04,251 --> 01:18:06,776
It's consistent with a.30-06 Enfield.

1168
01:18:07,754 --> 01:18:11,690
You'll be sorry. What happened to
that nigger will happen to you.

1169
01:18:13,060 --> 01:18:13,890
Another one?

1170
01:18:15,729 --> 01:18:19,756
Closer we get to trial, the more
nutjobs will crawl out of the woodwork.

1171
01:18:20,968 --> 01:18:21,866
You got a gun?

1172
01:18:23,403 --> 01:18:25,030
Here. T ake this.

1173
01:18:25,572 --> 01:18:27,437
No, wait. T ake this.

1174
01:18:29,076 --> 01:18:30,668
T ake this.

1175
01:18:55,002 --> 01:18:58,438
That was Muddy Waters doing
his thing for y'all.

1176
01:18:58,639 --> 01:19:01,631
Now I'll play a little something
that goes way back.

1177
01:19:01,842 --> 01:19:04,811
The great Robert Johnson.

1178
01:19:09,249 --> 01:19:10,307
Mr. Evers?

1179
01:19:13,687 --> 01:19:16,155
-Hi, I'm--
-Bobby DeLaughter.

1180
01:19:17,591 --> 01:19:19,320
Please sit down.

1181
01:19:29,169 --> 01:19:30,500
Robert Johnson.

1182
01:19:31,004 --> 01:19:33,234
IKing of the Delta Blues.

1183
01:19:36,076 --> 01:19:38,408
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

1184
01:19:40,981 --> 01:19:43,108
May your soul rise up to heaven...

1185
01:19:43,317 --> 01:19:45,785
...'fore the devil knows you're dead.

1186
01:19:52,292 --> 01:19:56,991
They say Robert Johnson sold his soul to
the devil to play the guitar like that.

1187
01:19:57,397 --> 01:19:58,295
What do you think?

1188
01:19:58,498 --> 01:20:02,798
If the devil wanted my soul, it'd cost
a lot more than some guitar lessons.

1189
01:20:06,039 --> 01:20:08,530
I believe after this trial's over...

1190
01:20:08,742 --> 01:20:11,176
...Mississippi come through this time.

1191
01:20:11,478 --> 01:20:14,345
That's why I came here
to talk with you, Mr. Evers.

1192
01:20:14,548 --> 01:20:18,416
Would you change your mind and come
to the trial? Your presence...

1193
01:20:18,618 --> 01:20:20,552
...would mean a great deal.

1194
01:20:22,389 --> 01:20:24,789
Let me tell you something.

1195
01:20:26,059 --> 01:20:28,550
Medgar was my baby brother.

1196
01:20:29,196 --> 01:20:31,960
There ain't nothing
I wouldn't do for him.

1197
01:20:33,033 --> 01:20:34,762
When we were little kids...

1198
01:20:34,968 --> 01:20:36,731
...we used to sleep in the same bed.

1199
01:20:36,937 --> 01:20:38,336
And on cold nights...

1200
01:20:38,538 --> 01:20:42,167
...I'd climb in first just so I could
warm up the sheets for him.

1201
01:20:44,745 --> 01:20:48,078
I didn't go to the first two trials.

1202
01:20:49,383 --> 01:20:50,907
Myrlie...

1203
01:20:51,585 --> 01:20:54,986
...a lot of people,
they criticized me for that.

1204
01:20:55,789 --> 01:20:58,417
But I won't go
to no third trial neither...

1205
01:20:59,459 --> 01:21:02,053
...and for the exact same reason.

1206
01:21:02,262 --> 01:21:06,289
I know if I ever got in the same room
with Byron De La Beckwith...

1207
01:21:06,500 --> 01:21:08,934
...as God is my witness...

1208
01:21:09,269 --> 01:21:12,761
...I'd wrap my hands around
his chicken neck and snap it in half.

1209
01:21:12,973 --> 01:21:14,702
And nobody...

1210
01:21:14,908 --> 01:21:16,842
...be able to stop me.

1211
01:21:18,512 --> 01:21:20,139
I wouldn't blame you.

1212
01:21:20,347 --> 01:21:21,575
Nobody hardly ever...

1213
01:21:21,782 --> 01:21:24,182
...remembers Medgar anymore.

1214
01:21:25,152 --> 01:21:27,017
Whites or blacks.

1215
01:21:27,687 --> 01:21:30,019
And that's a goddamn shame.

1216
01:21:30,757 --> 01:21:33,590
Because whatever rights
the black man has now...

1217
01:21:33,794 --> 01:21:37,127
...he's got because of something
called the Civil Rights Movement.

1218
01:21:37,330 --> 01:21:40,458
And for a long time here
in the state of Mississippi...

1219
01:21:40,967 --> 01:21:44,767
...before the television, newspapers,
back before the fancy speeches...

1220
01:21:44,971 --> 01:21:48,964
...my brother, Medgar, was
the Civil Rights Movement.

1221
01:21:54,614 --> 01:21:59,108
I'm sitting here tonight,
talking to my friend and your friend...

1222
01:21:59,319 --> 01:22:01,981
...Assistant District Attorney
Bobby DeLaughter.

1223
01:22:02,189 --> 01:22:05,317
We're talking about my brother,
Medgar Evers...

1224
01:22:05,525 --> 01:22:10,326
...and we're gonna play the blues
for Medgar all night long.

1225
01:22:20,841 --> 01:22:23,002
You and my sister-in-law...

1226
01:22:24,111 --> 01:22:26,045
...you get justice for my brother.

1227
01:22:35,822 --> 01:22:38,017
Devil, if you listening...

1228
01:22:38,258 --> 01:22:40,556
...I won't sell my soul
for no guitar lessons...

1229
01:22:40,760 --> 01:22:43,194
...but I'll sell my soul for that.

1230
01:22:47,834 --> 01:22:49,699
Are you surprised bail
was granted so quickly?

1231
01:22:49,903 --> 01:22:52,701
Mr. Beckwith was being held
as a political prisoner.

1232
01:22:52,906 --> 01:22:56,069
He's not been found guilty.
Why should he be kept in jail?

1233
01:22:57,444 --> 01:22:59,935
Mr. Scott, you're an officer
of the Nationalist Movement, correct?

1234
01:23:00,147 --> 01:23:02,479
Is that where the money came from
to secure his bond?

1235
01:23:02,682 --> 01:23:06,914
Mr. Beckwith has a lot of friends here.
We'll do whatever it takes.

1236
01:23:07,387 --> 01:23:11,619
Suppose he doesn't show for the trial?
Suppose he leaves the country?

1237
01:23:11,825 --> 01:23:13,884
If he runs, we'll find him.

1238
01:23:14,094 --> 01:23:15,823
How long will that take?

1239
01:23:16,029 --> 01:23:18,827
Another five years? Another 10?

1240
01:23:19,032 --> 01:23:23,059
I've already devoted a lifetime to this.
That ought to be enough.

1241
01:23:24,037 --> 01:23:26,562
Yes, ma'am. It sure ought to be.

1242
01:23:31,511 --> 01:23:33,138
I'm sorry, Bobby.

1243
01:23:34,247 --> 01:23:36,238
It's all right, Mrs. Evers.

1244
01:23:36,449 --> 01:23:37,939
It's quite all right.

1245
01:24:05,011 --> 01:24:07,571
-How's Jared doing?
-Fine.

1246
01:24:07,781 --> 01:24:11,046
He and Burt seem like
they've been brothers all their lives.

1247
01:24:11,251 --> 01:24:12,775
They all sleeping?

1248
01:24:14,454 --> 01:24:16,684
And that's what you should be doing.

1249
01:24:17,524 --> 01:24:19,719
I want the opening statement
to be great.

1250
01:24:20,493 --> 01:24:22,893
It was great when you read
it three nights ago.

1251
01:24:23,096 --> 01:24:25,030
Unless you snuck in something about...

1252
01:24:25,232 --> 01:24:27,325
...Beckwith deserving
the Nobel Peace Prize...

1253
01:24:27,534 --> 01:24:29,764
...I'm sure it'll be great
tomorrow morning.

1254
01:24:29,970 --> 01:24:32,495
You see? That's why I look to you.

1255
01:24:32,706 --> 01:24:36,164
Eliminate Nobel Peace Prize reference.

1256
01:24:36,376 --> 01:24:37,843
That's good.

1257
01:24:40,180 --> 01:24:44,446
I left a gift for you in appreciation
for everything you're doing...

1258
01:24:44,651 --> 01:24:46,516
... to ruin civilized society.

1259
01:24:46,720 --> 01:24:49,951
-What the hell is this?
-It's scheduled to go off at 10 p.m.

1260
01:24:50,156 --> 01:24:52,147
You have a nice night.

1261
01:24:56,663 --> 01:24:57,493
It's a bomb.

1262
01:25:02,502 --> 01:25:04,299
Everybody, get up.
Let's go.

1263
01:25:04,504 --> 01:25:05,869
What's going on?

1264
01:25:06,072 --> 01:25:09,974
It's nothing at all. Outside that door.
A little drill is all.

1265
01:25:10,176 --> 01:25:11,768
Head for the front door.

1266
01:25:45,912 --> 01:25:48,073
Is this still the drill?

1267
01:26:01,194 --> 01:26:02,752
Where are we going, Dad?

1268
01:26:02,962 --> 01:26:05,089
Told you we're going
to the Holiday Inn.

1269
01:26:05,298 --> 01:26:07,732
Is that where we're going?
The Holiday Inn?

1270
01:26:07,934 --> 01:26:08,832
That's right.

1271
01:26:09,035 --> 01:26:13,369
We haven't found anything,
but we'll go through it one more time.

1272
01:26:13,573 --> 01:26:15,404
I appreciate that.

1273
01:26:35,662 --> 01:26:40,258
I told them if anything ever happened,
all they had to do was walk away.

1274
01:26:42,435 --> 01:26:45,598
How're they supposed to walk away
from a bomb?

1275
01:26:50,577 --> 01:26:52,511
There wasn't a bomb.

1276
01:26:55,048 --> 01:26:56,515
This time.

1277
01:27:00,053 --> 01:27:02,920
If you want to give this thing up,
I understand.

1278
01:27:03,123 --> 01:27:06,650
No one could fault you. But the world
isn't going to be any safer.

1279
01:27:06,860 --> 01:27:09,727
I don't give a shit about the world.
These are my children.

1280
01:27:09,929 --> 01:27:11,260
Yes, they are.

1281
01:27:11,464 --> 01:27:13,955
Someday they'll be able
to tell their children...

1282
01:27:14,167 --> 01:27:16,897
...that their daddy put away
Medgar Evers' killer.

1283
01:27:17,470 --> 01:27:20,405
Medgar Evers was a fool,
and my daddy was right.

1284
01:27:20,607 --> 01:27:22,905
Doesn't matter how many
civil rights laws you pass.

1285
01:27:23,109 --> 01:27:25,407
You'll never legislate
how people think.

1286
01:27:25,612 --> 01:27:28,274
There are always gonna be
a few misguided people.

1287
01:27:28,481 --> 01:27:32,577
I'm not talking about a few people.
I'm talking about everybody, about us.

1288
01:27:32,786 --> 01:27:35,254
Do we have one single
black friend? No.

1289
01:27:35,455 --> 01:27:37,923
We don't have dinner with them
or have them over.

1290
01:27:38,124 --> 01:27:39,751
We don't sit with them in church.

1291
01:27:39,959 --> 01:27:42,757
You think this one trial will
magically change this?

1292
01:27:42,996 --> 01:27:44,657
No, I don't.

1293
01:27:45,131 --> 01:27:46,655
It's a step.

1294
01:27:47,400 --> 01:27:49,425
That's all anyone can do
is take a step.

1295
01:27:49,636 --> 01:27:51,763
Why do I have to take that step?

1296
01:27:51,971 --> 01:27:54,906
So some sick son of a bitch
can murder my wife and kids?

1297
01:27:55,108 --> 01:27:57,770
Excuse me if I'm not interested
in taking that step.

1298
01:27:57,977 --> 01:27:59,171
Where are you going?

1299
01:27:59,379 --> 01:28:01,142
For a drive.

1300
01:30:13,413 --> 01:30:17,782
" I don't know if I'm going to heaven
or hell, but I'm going from Jackson."

1301
01:30:20,820 --> 01:30:25,484
We're on record in the matter
of Mississippi v. Byron De La Beckwith.

1302
01:30:25,692 --> 01:30:27,819
Does prosecution have
its opening statement?

1303
01:30:29,329 --> 01:30:30,296
We do, Your Honor.

1304
01:30:36,536 --> 01:30:38,401
Ladies and gentlemen...

1305
01:30:38,605 --> 01:30:41,096
...this is a very simple case.

1306
01:30:43,076 --> 01:30:45,738
It's about a man whose life
was snuffed out...

1307
01:30:45,945 --> 01:30:49,312
...on June the 12th of 1963...

1308
01:30:49,916 --> 01:30:52,646
...by a bullet that tore
through his body.

1309
01:30:53,286 --> 01:30:56,221
A bullet aimed out of prejudice...

1310
01:30:56,422 --> 01:30:58,287
...propelled by hatred...

1311
01:30:58,491 --> 01:31:01,927
...and fired by
a back-shooting coward...

1312
01:31:03,062 --> 01:31:04,757
...from ambush...

1313
01:31:05,898 --> 01:31:06,990
...at night.

1314
01:31:07,533 --> 01:31:12,368
The evidence will overwhelmingly show
that Byron De La Beckwith...

1315
01:31:12,839 --> 01:31:16,275
...a self-proclaimed, rabid racist
on a lifelong mission...

1316
01:31:16,476 --> 01:31:19,274
...to purge society
of anyone and anything...

1317
01:31:19,479 --> 01:31:21,106
...that stood for integration...

1318
01:31:21,314 --> 01:31:23,839
...is the man that fired that bullet.

1319
01:31:24,417 --> 01:31:27,682
Evidence will show how, when he
thought he beat the system...

1320
01:31:27,887 --> 01:31:30,481
...he bragged about what he'd done.

1321
01:31:31,524 --> 01:31:34,891
Bragged about getting
away with murder.

1322
01:31:36,963 --> 01:31:41,093
The evidence will undeniably show that
the person who pulled the trigger...

1323
01:31:41,300 --> 01:31:45,327
...and ended the life of Medgar Evers
is this defendant...

1324
01:31:46,172 --> 01:31:48,231
...Byron De La Beckwith.

1325
01:31:52,745 --> 01:31:54,212
Mr. Coxwell?

1326
01:31:55,248 --> 01:31:56,840
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.

1327
01:31:57,283 --> 01:32:01,014
My name is Merrida Coxwell.
This is James Kitchens...

1328
01:32:01,220 --> 01:32:04,451
...and we are representing
Mr. Beckwith.

1329
01:32:05,058 --> 01:32:07,788
Mr. DeLaughter started
his opening statement...

1330
01:32:07,994 --> 01:32:10,963
...by saying that this was
a very simple case.

1331
01:32:11,164 --> 01:32:12,631
I agree with him.

1332
01:32:12,899 --> 01:32:16,892
But what Mr. DeLaughter is going
to rely on is for you...

1333
01:32:17,103 --> 01:32:21,699
...to convict Mr. Beckwith
simply because of his opinions.

1334
01:32:22,308 --> 01:32:23,468
That's because...

1335
01:32:23,676 --> 01:32:28,136
...he knows that the state cannot prove
to you beyond a reasonable doubt...

1336
01:32:28,347 --> 01:32:30,907
...that the defendant committed
the crime.

1337
01:32:31,117 --> 01:32:33,449
By the time this trial is over...

1338
01:32:33,653 --> 01:32:37,316
...you will have seen it was
physically impossible...

1339
01:32:37,523 --> 01:32:40,617
...for Mr. Byron De La Beckwith
to have killed Medgar Evers.

1340
01:32:40,960 --> 01:32:43,360
Mr. Beckwith is not guilty.

1341
01:32:43,563 --> 01:32:45,895
That's what the proof will show.

1342
01:32:46,499 --> 01:32:47,727
Thank you.

1343
01:32:49,635 --> 01:32:51,626
The state may call its first witness.

1344
01:32:52,905 --> 01:32:55,396
The state calls Myrlie Evers.

1345
01:33:08,387 --> 01:33:09,752
Raise your right hand.

1346
01:33:09,956 --> 01:33:11,981
Do you swear to tell the truth...

1347
01:33:12,191 --> 01:33:14,955
-...the whole truth, so help you God?
-I do.

1348
01:33:15,228 --> 01:33:16,525
Be seated.

1349
01:33:22,769 --> 01:33:24,532
Will you tell us your name?

1350
01:33:25,104 --> 01:33:27,197
My name is Myrlie Evers.

1351
01:33:27,406 --> 01:33:30,500
Going back to 1963,
were you married at that time?

1352
01:33:30,710 --> 01:33:32,143
Yes, I was.

1353
01:33:32,345 --> 01:33:34,176
And to whom were you married?

1354
01:33:36,916 --> 01:33:38,781
Medgar Wylie...

1355
01:33:38,985 --> 01:33:40,475
...Evers.

1356
01:33:46,793 --> 01:33:49,785
When was the last time
you saw your husband alive?

1357
01:33:50,663 --> 01:33:53,359
June 11, 1963.

1358
01:33:55,034 --> 01:33:57,093
I'd fallen behind...

1359
01:33:57,303 --> 01:34:00,466
...in my housework
and got up early that morning...

1360
01:34:00,740 --> 01:34:03,231
...to iron some shirts for Medgar.

1361
01:34:04,610 --> 01:34:06,100
By the time he woke...

1362
01:34:06,312 --> 01:34:10,646
...I had 10 freshly ironed shirts
neatly hung on hangers.

1363
01:34:12,185 --> 01:34:15,450
He said, "I thank you
for ironing these shirts...

1364
01:34:15,655 --> 01:34:17,418
...but I'm not going to need them."

1365
01:34:18,858 --> 01:34:22,851
Before he left for work that morning,
he kissed us all goodbye...

1366
01:34:23,262 --> 01:34:25,162
...and then left.

1367
01:34:26,532 --> 01:34:28,124
But then he came back...

1368
01:34:28,334 --> 01:34:30,427
...and took me aside.

1369
01:34:30,837 --> 01:34:33,328
He said, "If anything
should happen to me...

1370
01:34:33,539 --> 01:34:35,598
...I want you to promise me...

1371
01:34:35,808 --> 01:34:38,504
...you will take care of my babies."

1372
01:34:39,445 --> 01:34:42,812
I said, "Of course.
They're my babies too."

1373
01:34:45,251 --> 01:34:48,846
He then kissed us all
goodbye again and left.

1374
01:34:51,858 --> 01:34:54,258
Could you tell the jury
what you remember...

1375
01:34:54,460 --> 01:34:58,419
...seeing and hearing when your husband
returned home that night?

1376
01:34:59,098 --> 01:35:02,625
It was just after midnight
when he got home.

1377
01:35:03,469 --> 01:35:05,300
We heard the car.

1378
01:35:13,746 --> 01:35:16,214
And then there was...

1379
01:35:20,553 --> 01:35:23,147
...this horrible blast.

1380
01:35:25,691 --> 01:35:27,318
The children...

1381
01:35:28,027 --> 01:35:31,258
...fell to the floor
as their father had taught them.

1382
01:35:32,265 --> 01:35:34,825
I bolted to the front door.

1383
01:35:36,202 --> 01:35:39,069
Medgar was lying in the carport.

1384
01:35:40,306 --> 01:35:42,831
He still had his keys in his hand.

1385
01:35:45,044 --> 01:35:47,410
Blood everywhere.

1386
01:35:49,148 --> 01:35:51,776
The children came out
shortly after I did...

1387
01:35:51,984 --> 01:35:53,849
...and they were screaming...

1388
01:35:54,854 --> 01:35:56,014
... "Daddy!

1389
01:35:57,056 --> 01:35:58,580
Daddy, get up!

1390
01:36:00,393 --> 01:36:02,361
Daddy, please get up."

1391
01:36:05,965 --> 01:36:08,866
But I knew he would
never get up again.

1392
01:36:13,873 --> 01:36:15,773
Nothing further, Your Honor.

1393
01:36:17,877 --> 01:36:22,940
Mr. McIntyre, have you ever owned
a 1917 Enfield.30-06 rifle?

1394
01:36:23,749 --> 01:36:24,943
Yes, I have.

1395
01:36:25,151 --> 01:36:27,881
Did you own that rifle in 1963?

1396
01:36:28,821 --> 01:36:33,622
Sometime, I believe in 1960,
I traded it to Mr. Beckwith.

1397
01:36:33,893 --> 01:36:37,954
Mr. McIntyre, I want to show you
this firearm and ask if you would...

1398
01:36:38,164 --> 01:36:41,395
...read the serial number
on the barrel, please.

1399
01:36:42,101 --> 01:36:46,037
1-0-5-2-6-8-2.

1400
01:36:46,238 --> 01:36:50,299
Thank you. Going back to exhibit 35,
would you read the serial number...

1401
01:36:50,509 --> 01:36:52,977
...on the invoice of the gun
that you purchased...

1402
01:36:53,179 --> 01:36:55,238
...and later traded to Mr. Beckwith?

1403
01:36:55,448 --> 01:36:59,111
1-0-5-2-6-8-2.

1404
01:36:59,618 --> 01:37:03,987
Ms. Holder, were you at Joe's Drive-In
on the night of June 11, 1963?

1405
01:37:04,190 --> 01:37:05,316
Yes, sir.

1406
01:37:05,524 --> 01:37:09,255
I wasn't working, but I was there
hanging out with my friends.

1407
01:37:09,762 --> 01:37:12,890
T ell the jury if there came
a time when your attention...

1408
01:37:13,099 --> 01:37:15,590
...was directed towards
any particular automobile.

1409
01:37:17,603 --> 01:37:20,333
Being a carhop, you notice cars.

1410
01:37:20,539 --> 01:37:23,702
This one had a long antenna
on the side of it.

1411
01:37:23,909 --> 01:37:26,343
We thought at first
it was a patrol car.

1412
01:37:26,979 --> 01:37:29,948
It was white and it had
a lot of mud on it.

1413
01:37:30,983 --> 01:37:32,780
It was a Plymouth Valiant.

1414
01:37:32,985 --> 01:37:37,752
Mr. Hargrove, were you employed by the
Jackson Police Department in June 1963?

1415
01:37:37,957 --> 01:37:39,686
Yes, I was.

1416
01:37:39,892 --> 01:37:43,623
In charge of the ldentification Division
for 42 years.

1417
01:37:43,829 --> 01:37:46,957
Did you reach a conclusion
as to whose fingerprint...

1418
01:37:47,166 --> 01:37:49,600
...was on the telescopic side
of the gun...

1419
01:37:49,802 --> 01:37:54,068
...recovered in your presence
on June 12, 1963?

1420
01:37:54,407 --> 01:37:55,669
Yes, sir. I did.

1421
01:37:55,875 --> 01:37:59,174
With 14 points of identification,
there's more than enough...

1422
01:37:59,378 --> 01:38:02,711
...to identify the fingerprint
of Mr. Byron De La Beckwith.

1423
01:38:03,015 --> 01:38:07,281
After four days of testimony in the
trial of white supremacist Beckwith...

1424
01:38:07,486 --> 01:38:10,887
...the prosecution, thus far, has
presented essentially the same case...

1425
01:38:11,090 --> 01:38:12,387
...as was offered up
in the two original trials.

1426
01:38:14,326 --> 01:38:17,454
However, this time there are
two significant differences.

1427
01:38:17,663 --> 01:38:19,722
First, the makeup of the jury.

1428
01:38:19,932 --> 01:38:24,062
In 1964, Beckwith faced
two all-male, all-white juries.

1429
01:38:24,270 --> 01:38:27,899
Today, he faces a jury made up
of eight blacks and four whites.

1430
01:38:28,107 --> 01:38:32,237
Tomorrow the prosecution is expected
to introduce three new witnesses...

1431
01:38:32,445 --> 01:38:35,107
... who did not testify
in the first two trials.

1432
01:38:37,283 --> 01:38:39,274
State your name for the record.

1433
01:38:39,485 --> 01:38:40,918
Delmar Dennis.

1434
01:38:41,120 --> 01:38:43,520
Mr. Dennis, in March of 1964...

1435
01:38:43,722 --> 01:38:45,849
...were you a member
of an organization known as...

1436
01:38:46,058 --> 01:38:47,958
...the White Knights
of the Ku Klux Klan?

1437
01:38:48,160 --> 01:38:49,286
I was.

1438
01:38:49,495 --> 01:38:51,019
In September of that year...

1439
01:38:51,230 --> 01:38:54,131
...did you become
a paid informant for the FBl?

1440
01:38:54,333 --> 01:38:55,595
I did.

1441
01:38:55,801 --> 01:38:57,701
And in your capacity as informant...

1442
01:38:57,903 --> 01:39:01,498
...did you ever encounter
the defendant, Byron De La Beckwith?

1443
01:39:02,208 --> 01:39:03,539
I did.

1444
01:39:04,543 --> 01:39:06,977
What were the circumstances
of that encounter?

1445
01:39:07,713 --> 01:39:10,841
On August 8, 1965,
I met Mr. Beckwith...

